@startmindmap
title FIG-20-01. Choosing the Right Infrastructure and Deployment View
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
' Original beginner selection guide derived from Chapter 20.
' Meaning is carried by text, not colour.
* Start with the\noperational question
** Runtime placement
*** What runs where?
**** UML or C4\ndeployment view
** Connectivity
*** Which zones and\ntraffic paths matter?
**** Network topology
** Cloud responsibility
*** Which cloud services\nand responsibilities matter?
**** Cloud architecture view
** Cluster workload
*** Which Kubernetes resources\nrun and connect workloads?
**** Kubernetes\ndeployment view
** Environment
*** What is deliberately different\nbetween environments?
**** Environment\ncomparison matrix
** Continuity
*** How does service continue\nthrough expected failure?
**** Availability or\nresilience view
*** How is service restored\nafter serious disruption?
**** Recovery view
** Operations
*** Who knows, acts\nand escalates?
**** Ownership matrix or\nobservability view
** Still unclear?
*** Clarify audience, boundary,\nenvironment and decision
**** Do not choose a view\nuntil the question is specific
@endmindmap
